2 Types of IPv6 includes, Global Unicast Addresses (GUA) and Link-Local Addresses (LLA). GUA focuses on Public IPv4 addresses, internet access, the router forwards packets, Automated, prefix range is “2000::/3”, while LLA focuses on MAC addresses/Private Addresses, routing, it does drop router packets, prefix range “FE80::/10”.
